{"id":8058,"date":"2023-10-06T20:07:36","date_gmt":"2023-10-07T03:07:36","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.exteriorcrew.com\/?p=8058"},"modified":"2023-10-06T22:58:25","modified_gmt":"2023-10-07T05:58:25","slug":"warranty-for-siding-installation","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.exteriorcrew.com\/blog\/warranty-for-siding-installation\/","title":{"rendered":"Understanding the Warranty: What to Expect from Your Siding Company"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>The exterior of a home serves as the first line of defense against the elements. And a critical component of this protection is siding. Beyond aesthetic appeal, siding keeps out moisture, guards against pests, and more. With such an essential role, understanding the warranty for siding installation is topmost for homeowners. This article dives into what you should expect from your siding company regarding warranties.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><strong>Why Warranties are Important<\/strong><\/span><\/p>\n<p>When investing in a siding replacement project, a warranty for siding installation is not just a piece of paper; it offers peace of mind by providing:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Protection for your investment:<\/strong> Siding is not cheap. Warranties ensure you get value for your money.<\/li>\n<li><strong>Assurance of quality workmanship:<\/strong> The best materials can fail if poorly installed. A warranty is a company\u2019s promise of professional installation.<\/li>\n<li><strong>Use of premium materials:<\/strong> A warranty often suggests the siding material meets specific quality benchmarks.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3><strong style=\"font-size: 24px; color: inherit; font-family: inherit;\">Types of Warranties for Siding<\/strong><\/h3>\n<p>Understanding the distinctions between warranty types is essential.<\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\"><strong>Manufacturer\u2019s Warranty<\/strong><\/span><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Typically covers defects in the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.jameshardiepros.com\/getattachment\/db50c299-864b-4bb0-89c0-b4a0800fad11\/rs2093-hs11124.pdf\">material<\/a>.<\/li>\n<li>Often excludes damage from installation errors, hence the need for the second warranty type.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\"><strong>Workmanship Warranty<\/strong><\/span><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>This speaks directly to the quality of the installation.<\/li>\n<li>Duration can vary, but always ensure that it complements the manufacturer&#8217;s warranty.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h3><\/h3>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3><strong style=\"font-size: 24px; color: inherit; font-family: inherit;\">Key Components to Look for in a Siding Warranty<\/strong><\/h3>\n<p>Warranties vary. Here are some key parts to keep an eye on:<\/p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Coverage Period:<\/strong> Does the warranty cover short-term or extend for many years? Longer durations often indicate higher confidence in the product or work.<\/li>\n<li><strong>Transferability:<\/strong> If you sell your home, can the new owner benefit from the warranty? This adds value to your property.<\/li>\n<li><strong>Exclusions and Limitations:<\/strong> While all warranties have them, understanding what&#8217;s not covered helps avoid future disputes.<\/li>\n<li><strong>Maintenance Requirements:<\/strong> Some warranties might become void if you neglect maintenance. Be aware of any such terms.<\/li>\n<li><strong>Claims Process:<\/strong> Knowing the steps to claim, and the expected resolution timeline, is crucial for peace of mind.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<p><strong>\u00a0<\/strong><\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><strong>The Role of the Siding Company in Upholding the Warranty<\/strong><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>Your chosen siding company is the bridge between you and your warranty\u2019s promises.<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Prompt Response to Issues:<\/strong> A reputable company will address concerns quickly.<\/li>\n<li><strong>Commitment to Quality:<\/strong> A company\u2019s reputation is often linked to its warranty service. Research reviews and testimonials.<\/li>\n<li><strong>Regular Check-ins: <\/strong>Some companies might offer maintenance as part of the warranty. This can be invaluable.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><strong>Red Flags: When to Be Skeptical of a Warranty<\/strong><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>Not all warranties are created equal. Be cautious of:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Too Good to Be True Promises:<\/strong> A lifetime warranty might sound appealing, but what does it truly cover?<\/li>\n<li><strong>Vague Language:<\/strong> Ambiguities can lead to disputes. Clarity is essential.<\/li>\n<li><strong>Hidden Costs:<\/strong> Ensure there aren\u2019t unexpected fees when making a claim.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\"><strong>Tips for Making the Most of Your Warranty<\/strong><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>To maximize your warranty:<\/p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Keep All Documentation:<\/strong> This includes bids, receipts, and warranty certificates.<\/li>\n<li><strong>Conduct Annual Inspections:<\/strong> Protect your siding by conducting regular inspections of your home\u2019s exterior.<\/li>\n<li><strong>Establish Open Communication with Your Siding Company:<\/strong> This helps in ensuring any concerns are addressed promptly.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<p>Understanding the warranty for siding installation is more than just due diligence; it\u2019s securing the future of your home\u2019s exterior. Knowing what to expect, and what is expected of you, provides a smooth, worry-free experience with your siding company. Secure your home, and your peace of mind, by being informed and prepared.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\"><strong>To conclude, here&#8217;s a glimpse of the Exterior Crew\u2019s workmanship warranty:<\/strong><\/span><\/h3>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/www.exteriorcrew.com\/seattle-siding-company-for-homeowners\/\">Exterior Crew<\/a> offers a 5-year warranty on all workmanship from the date of substantial completion of your project. If the home is sold, the warranty transfers to the new owner for the remaining duration. While we commit to installing siding per manufacturer specifications, our warranty covers only our workmanship, not material failures outside of installation. No specific maintenance is required by homeowners to uphold our workmanship warranty. If a workmanship-related siding issue arises, we commit to addressing the claim within 72 hours; if the defect is due to our installation, we&#8217;ll resolve it within 30 working days.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>The exterior of a home serves as the first line of defense against the elements. And a critical component of this protection is siding. Beyond aesthetic appeal, siding keeps out moisture, guards against pests, and more. With such an essential role, understanding the warranty for siding installation is topmost for homeowners. This article dives into [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":13,"featured_media":8059,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"footnotes":""},"categories":[28],"tags":[],"yoast_head":"<!-- This site is optimized with the Yoast SEO Premium plugin v20.9 (Yoast SEO v20.9) - https:\/\/yoast.com\/wordpress\/plugins\/seo\/ -->\n<title>Essentials of a Warranty for Siding Installation Explained<\/title>\n<meta name=\"description\" content=\"Uncover the essentials of a warranty for siding installation, it\u2019s types, key elements, and maximizing benefits. Get insights on Exterior Crew\u2019s warranty.\" \/>\n<meta name=\"robots\" content=\"index, follow, max-snippet:-1, max-image-preview:large, max-video-preview:-1\" \/>\n<link rel=\"canonical\" href=\"https:\/\/www.exteriorcrew.com\/blog\/warranty-for-siding-installation\/\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:locale\" content=\"en_US\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:type\" content=\"article\" \/>\n<m